&lt;p&gt;As Clinical Network Managers, the successful candidates will work as part of a dynamic team in delivering a programme of work that supports and enables the wider delivery of health and care improvement across STPS and ICSs in our South West region and that is in line with national priorities for cardiovascular, respiratory and diabetes services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Post holders will manage and lead on a portfolio of projects that support the delivery of the clinical networks programme and to act as project leader – planning, and co-ordinating the delivery of the project, working with others and engaging the constituency of the network as necessary.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Clinical Networks bring stakeholders together – providers, commissioners and patients – to create alignment around programmes of transformational work that will improve care for the health economy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Due to COVID-19 this will be predominately home based at present.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Office base: Saltash/Bristol/Taunton/Chippenham&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; Please note that the reason for the 2 year fixed term/secondment contract is due to funds being from limited programme funding.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
